---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/layout/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/layout/Footer.astro';
import StandingLine from '../components/ui/StandingLine.astro';
import EmergencyBoundary from '../components/ui/EmergencyBoundary.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Security & Privacy at Liaison.legal — In Plain English"
  description="How Liaison.legal protects your co-parenting records: SHA-256 hashing, tamper-evident chaining, encryption in transit and at rest, and strict access controls. Explained plainly."
>
  <Nav />
  <main>

    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="bg-gray-100 py-20 px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h1 class="font-display font-bold text-4xl md:text-5xl text-navy mb-6">
          Security &amp; privacy, explained in plain English.
        </h1>
        <p class="font-body text-lg text-slate leading-relaxed">
          Your co-parenting record may end up in front of a judge. Here's exactly how we protect
          it — and what we will and won't say about it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Answer-first -->
    <section class="bg-white py-10 px-6 border-b border-gray-200">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <p class="font-body text-base text-slate leading-relaxed">
          Liaison.legal protects co-parenting records with cryptographic hashing (SHA-256), a
          tamper-evident hash chain linking each message to the one before it, encryption in
          transit and at rest, and strict access controls over who can ever view a record.
          Messages can't be quietly edited or deleted after they're sent. Attorneys get access
          only to their own client's record, and only the parties to a matter and their authorized
          professionals can see it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Sections -->
    <section class="bg-white py-20 px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-16">

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl text-navy mb-4">
            What "tamper-evident" means
          </h2>
          <p class="font-body text-base text-slate leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Every message is run through SHA-256 — a one-way cryptographic fingerprint — and each
            fingerprint is chained to the one before it. If anyone tried to alter or remove a past
            message, the chain would break and the change would be detectable. That's what lets
            your record answer the question every court asks: <em>can we trust that this wasn't
            changed after the fact?</em>
          </p>
          <p class="font-body text-sm text-gray-400 italic">
            (We say "tamper-evident," not "immutable," because it's the accurate word: the
            integrity of the record is verifiable.)
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl text-navy mb-4">
            Who can see your messages
          </h2>
          <p class="font-body text-base text-slate leading-relaxed">
            Messages are encrypted in transit and at rest. Access is tightly controlled: only the
            parties to a matter and the professionals they authorize can view a record. Attorney
            access is limited to that attorney's own client. We are honest about one thing many
            apps gloss over — when an attorney activates the forensic audit on a matter, the
            system processes the messages on that matter to perform the analysis. We don't pretend
            a tool that reads the record can't read the record. What we promise is that access is
            controlled, limited, logged, and never sold.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl text-navy mb-4">
            What we never do with your data
          </h2>
          <ul class="space-y-3 font-body text-base text-slate">
            {[
              'We never sell or share your data with advertisers.',
              'We never run ads against your record.',
              'We never show one parent the other parent\'s private notes or an attorney\'s work product.',
              'We never surface the forensic audit or its findings to parents.',
            ].map((item) => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-azure font-bold mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0">✓</span>
                {item}
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl text-navy mb-4">
            What Liaison.legal is not
          </h2>
          <p class="font-body text-base text-slate leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Liaison.legal is a record-keeping tool. It is <strong>not</strong> a law firm and
            does <strong>not</strong> provide legal advice. It is <strong>not</strong> an
            emergency service — if you or your child are in immediate danger, call 911 or your
            local emergency number. And it is <strong>not</strong> a substitute for a protective
            order or other legal protection.
          </p>
          <StandingLine />
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="bg-gray-100 py-12 px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
        <p class="font-body text-base text-slate">
          Have a specific question?
          <a href="/faq" class="text-azure hover:underline ml-1">See the FAQ →</a>
          <span class="mx-2 text-gray-400">·</span>
          <a href="mailto:info@liaison.legal" class="text-azure hover:underline">Contact us →</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
